    <h1 class="opener__hed  opener__hed--light opener__hed--small" >        He Was Convicted of Killing His Baby. The DA’s Office Says He’s Innocent, but That Might Not Be Enough.
    </h1>

    
            <div class="article-meta-1  article-meta-1--light">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/pamela-colloff">Pamela Colloff</a>, photography by <span class="name">Stacy Kranitz</span>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-07-11EDT05:00">July 11, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

            <div class="content"> <!-- not sure if this is the best way to reestablish the text column -->
            <h2 class="opener__dek opener__dek--match-text-column" >                When new scientific evidence casts doubt on convictions, the justice system has no easy path to freedom — even when it’s the prosecutors doing the asking.
            </h2>
        </div>
    
</div>
        
